  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by initiating restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the guidelines for this amount and lack of criminal history suggest a short custodial sentence combined with probation and mandatory repayment is appropriate. The outburst from the courtroom spectator is irrelevant to the legal merits of the case. A sentence of 8 months balances the punitive nature of the law with the opportunity for rehabilitation and continued restitution.",
  "verdict": 8
}
